name: machine operation, diesel, < 18.64 kW, generators | machine operation, diesel, < 18.64 kW, generators | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10619/documentation

This dataset represents the operation of commercial generators. The U.S. EPA NONROAD2008 model for off-road machines has been used as basis for this dataset, it refers to engine power in units of horsepower (hp), the engine power range for the dataset is then < 25 hp. The fuel consumption and emission factors from the model have been kept in the original units of kg/hp.hour for transparency reasons. However the engine power parameter used as input data for the dataset is quantified in the SI power unit of kilowatt (kW). The functional unit is 1 hour of operation.;The fuel consumption and basic emission factors are generated by the U.S. EPA NONROAD2008 model for off-road machines. Supplementary emissions are provided by the U.S. EPA NMIM model and copied directly from the ecoinvent v3.0 dataset "diesel burned in building machine, GLO 2001". The building machine infrastructure and lubricating oil input and waste output have been copied from the same ecoinvent dataset. ;This dataset is a template dataset and has been parameterized for the machine power (in kW), emission standard (referred to as "tier" by the U.S EPA, the European equivalents would be the Stage I to IV standards published by the European Commission) and load factor to enable the creation of specific instances. To do so, the tier fraction (e.g. T0) and power (e.g. T0_kW), and the load factor parameters could be changed to reflect a specific situation/machine. The diesel fuel sulfur content (see Exchange Properties) could also be changed (the ultra-low sulfur nonroad diesel sulfur content of 0,0015% or 15 ppm, effective June 2010 in the United States of America is used as default).



Includes the inputs " building machine" for infrastructure, lubricating oil and fuel consumption, and air emissions and waste oil as outputs.

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Fuel flow and most emission flows are extrapolated from US conditions, some emission flows and the other intermediate product flows (building machine, lubricating oil) are extrapolated from RER and CH conditions. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Average current technology for one typical machine representing the category.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Most data from the U.S. EPA NONROAD2008 and NMIM models. Some data from the LCA study Oekoinventare von Energiesystemen 1996 and emissions from the Swiss "Offroad" database.

Calculated value. Represents the emissions per hour of operation of the US weigthed average machine represented by this dataset (< 18.64 kW, generators). Based on the diesel fuel sulfur content, modulated by the estimated fraction of sulfur directly converted to particulate form (value of 0,978 taken from NONROAD2008 model). The value of 2 in the mathematical relation repressents the stoichiometric relationship between sulfur dioxide and elementary sulfur (2 g SO2/g S).

exchanges.description: Calculated value. Represents the emissions per hour of operation of the US weigthed average machine represented by this dataset (< 18.64 kW, generators). Based on the carbon balance, considers the diesel fuel carbon content and the carbon in the other carbon containing emissions and converts the remaining into carbon dioxide. The 44/12 term represents the stoichiometric relationship between carbon dioxide and carbon.
